==English==

===Noun===
'''La-La Land''' (''singular'')

# The [[fictional]] place where [[wander]]ing, [[sleep]]ing, or [[dream]]ing minds are [[metaphor]]ically said to end up; usually used in reference to people who are not paying any attention.
Kuro: #: ''Oh, don't mind him, he's usually up in '''La-La Land''', with all his silly ideas, you douchebag.''
Mari: #: ''Are you paying attention?  Come back from '''La-La Land'''!''
Fas: ...OMG NOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO!

